                "",
                "Like Legal Counselors: See the Bach who brings here the Talmudic passage about the matter regarding the relatives of Rav Nachman, and he wrote, quote: “We can derive from this that if it wasn’t an important person, there is no prohibition of preparing before the judges proofs for the benefit of his relative, or to teach his relative correct claims,” end quote. And see the Tosafot Yom Tov in the first chapter of Avot, Mishna 8, that it seems to him that an unimportant person, even if he is not related to him, it is permitted, and he then brings the words of Rashi that proves that if they are not related, it is not permitted, see there..."
